From 62f592f0ff1b833391ae6c866984234b754b5a5a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 15:35:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add pgBackRest integration for PostgreSQL incremental
 backups

Implements pgBackRest as an alternative backup engine for PostgreSQL databases,
enabling incremental and differential backups that significantly reduce storage
costs and backup time for large databases (100GB+).

Changes:
- Add PgBackrestService with config generation, S3 support, WAL archiving
- Modify DatabaseBackupJob to support pgBackRest engine alongside pg_dump
- Modify StartPostgresql to configure WAL archiving when pgBackRest is enabled
- Add backup engine selection UI (pg_dump vs pgBackRest) in Livewire components
- Add database migration for engine/backup_type columns
- Add comprehensive unit tests for PgBackrestService
- PSR-12 compliant (camelCase methods, proper authorization)
- Error handling in installation scripts with verification

Resolves #7423
